{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idaa7a52ff-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s4403"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4403"},"text":"§ 4403.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Requirements relating to availability of major system interfaces and support for modular open system approach","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary of each military department shall—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa7a5300-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s4403/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" coordinate with the other military departments, the defense agencies, defense and other private sector entities, national standards-setting organizations, and, when appropriate, with elements of the intelligence community with respect to the specification, identification, development, and maintenance of major system interfaces and standards for use in major system platforms, where practicable;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa7a5301-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s4403/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" ensure major system interfaces are adequately designated and defined to achieve a modular open system approach and are delivered with supporting documentation necessary to enable the integration of components or modules provided by a third party into the modular system;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa7a5302-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s4403/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" ensure that sufficient systems engineering and development expertise and resources are available to support the use of a modular open system approach in requirements development and acquisition program planning;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa7a5303-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s4403/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" ensure that necessary planning, programming, and budgeting resources are provided to specify, identify, develop, and sustain the modular open system approach, associated major system interfaces, systems integration, and any additional program activities necessary to sustain innovation and interoperability;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa7a5304-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s4403/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" ensure that adequate training in the use of a modular open system approach is provided to members of the requirements and acquisition workforce; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa7a5305-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s4403/6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"(6)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" issue guidance to implement the requirements of this section.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idaa7a5306-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/328/dA/tVIII/s805/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–328, div. A, title VIII, § 805(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2016-12-23"},"text":"Dec. 23, 2016","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/130/2255"},"text":"130 Stat. 2255","children":[],"tail":", § 2446c; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/92/dA/tVIII/s840/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–92, div. A, title VIII, § 840(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2019-12-20"},"text":"Dec. 20, 2019","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/133/1499"},"text":"133 Stat. 1499","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 4403, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/dA/tXVIII/s1851/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, div. A, title XVIII, § 1851(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 2021","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/134/4272"},"text":"134 Stat. 4272","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/119/60/dA/tXVIII/s1832/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 119–60, div. A, title XVIII, § 1832(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2025-12-18"},"text":"Dec. 18, 2025","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/139/1253"},"text":"139 Stat. 1253","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idaa7a5307-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idaa7a5308-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"idaa7a5309-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Prior sections 4411 to 4414 were renumbered sections 7481 to 7484 of this title, respectively.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior s